Name: Greens: Spinach (1/3 lb)
Body: Fresh picked spinach, straight from the high tunnel. As over-wintered spinach, it has an extra delicious sweetness. In a 1/3 pound bag.

Name: Greens: Deluxe Salad Mix (5 oz bag)
Body: Salad mix made of eight types of baby lettuce, sunflower shoots, and pea shoots. In 5-oz bag.

Name: Greens: Curly Kale (bu)
Body: Bunch of fresh curly kale – The essential hearty green! Our kale is sweet, on top of being a nutritional powerhouse.

Name: Greens: Rainbow Swiss Chard (bu)
Body: Rainbow Swiss Chard is an earthy-flavored green, more delicate than kale. Use the stems as well as the greens in soups, frittatas, stir fry, and more!

Name: Greens: Collard Greens (bu)
Body: Winter-harvested collard greens lend a sweet hearty flavor to any meal - broad, thick leaves with rich, dark green coloring.

Name: Greens: Red Russian Kale (bu)
Body: The best winter kale - soft, tender leaves, beautiful green and lavender coloring.

Name: Mei Qing (Bok Choy)
Body: One large lead of delicious bok choy, perfect for sauteing!  Misty-green stems form a thick, heavy base with broad, oval, rich green leaves.

Name: Arugula
Body: 5 ounce bag of fresh-cut arugula - the perfect sharp flavor for your salad or wrap!

Name: Greens: Parsley, bunch
Body: One bunch of fresh, flat-leave parsley.

Name: Cabbage: Napa Cabbage
Body: Hearty napa cabbages - note that the cabbages are $1.50 per pound (the same price as at farmers market).

Name: Cabbage: Napa Cabbage
Body: Hearty napa cabbages - note that the cabbages are $1.50 per pound (the same price as at farmers market).

Name: Cabbage: Green Cabbage
Body: Sweet winter cabbages -note that the cabbages are $2 per pound (the same price as at farmers market).  So there are a variety of size options here - choose the the size cabbage you'd like, and the price should match the weight.

Name: Cabbage: Green Cabbage
Body: Sweet winter cabbages -note that the cabbages are $2 per pound (the same price as at farmers market).  So there are a variety of size options here - choose the the size cabbage you'd like, and the price should match the weight.

Name: Cabbage: Green Cabbage
Body: Sweet winter cabbages -note that the cabbages are $2 per pound (the same price as at farmers market).  So there are a variety of size options here - choose the the size cabbage you'd like, and the price should match the weight.

Name: Power Greens
Body: A bag of delicious power greens - baby mustard, baby kale, and baby tokyo bekana (a mild tender Asian green).  A 5-oz bag of triple-washed greens.

Name: Koji Tatsoi
Body: Dark green, hybrid tatsoi with cupped, heavy leaves are beautifully savoyed and borne on long, elegant stems.

Name: Greens: Head Lettuce
Body: One large head of fresh lettuce!  If heads are small, we will sub two small for one large.

Name: Italian Dandeion
Body: Tender and uniform Italian dandelion - slightly bitter, great for fresh eating.

Name: Mushrooms: Shiitake
Body: From Wiltbank Farm in Saugerties, these shiitake mushrooms are fresh, meaty, and flavorful.  Sold in 1/2 pound bag (approximately 1 quart).

Name: Mushrooms: Oyster
Body: From Wiltbank Farm in Saugerties, these oyster mushrooms are fresh and delicate in texture, but big on flavor.  Sold in 1/2 lb bag.

Name: Garlic (medium size)
Body: Medium-sized German White garlic, great flavor for a variety of uses. Usually 4-5 cloves per head.

Name: Squash: Butternut Squash
Body: The king of winter squash. Excellent sweet flavor, great for roasting, soups, and more.  Butternuts are $1.50 per pound, most squash are multiple pounds.

Name: Tree Juice Maple Syrup - half gallon
Body: A half gallon of the sweet stuff!  Get a half gallon of delicious dark maple syrup, courtesy of our friends at Tree Juice.

Name: 2 lb Wildflower Honey from Damn Good Honey
Body: Pure unfiltered, unprocessed wildflower honey from Kerhonkson, NY.  Comes in a 2 lb jar.

Name: Old Ford Farm Eggs, one dozen
Body: We picked up some eggs from Old Ford Farm that are up for grabs - order them while we've got them!

Name: Squash: Koginut Squash
Body: A new-on-the-scene winter squash with deep, smoky sweetness and a creamy texture. Koginuts are $2.00 per pound, most squash are multiple pounds.  Note that you have the option to choose the squash size, as well as a quantity.

Name: Squash: Koginut Squash
Body: A new-on-the-scene winter squash with deep, smoky sweetness and a creamy texture. Koginuts are $2.00 per pound, most squash are multiple pounds.  Note that you have the option to choose the squash size, as well as a quantity.

Name: Sweet Potatoes - 2 lb
Body: Amazingly sweet and healthy - two pounds of sweet potatoes for roasting, mashing, frying - you name it!

Name: Food Pantry Donation
Body: This winter Solid Ground will be making regular food donations to local food banks - add this donation item to your cart to bolster the donation effort with $10 of additional produce.

Name: Winter Radish Mix (2 lb)
Body: A medley of our four delicious winter radishes - daikon, watermelon, green luobo, and black spanish.  Makes a great choice if you want some diversity in your roots, or if you'd like to do a taste test to determine your favorite radish.  Comes in a two-pound mix bag.

Name: Root Roast Mix (2 lb)
Body: A little bit of everything - beets, carrots, purple-top white globe turnips, and winter radishes.  Makes a perfect root bake - scrub, cube, oil and salt, and bake on a cookie sheet.  Or use in soups, mashes, more!  Comes in a two-pound mix bag.

Name: Roots: Beets - per lb.
Body: Red beets by the lb -- deep, vibrant red, beets are great roasted, boiled and sliced in a salad, or even fermented!

Name: Roots: Purple Top Turnip - per lb.
Body: Purple top turnips by the lb -- great for roasting, mashing, and soups, turnips are less starchy than rutabagas and have a slightly aromatic flavor.

Name: Roots: Daikon Radish
Body: Daikon radish  -- white, spicy, super crisp, great for fresh eating, pickling, kimchi, and roasting.

Name: Roots: Green Luobo Radish - per lb.
Body: Green luobo radish by the lb -- green and white, strong and spicy with an underlying sweetness, great for fresh eating, pickling, kimchi, and roasting.

Name: Roots: Black Spanish Radish - per lb.
Body: Black spanish radish by the lb - black skin and white on the inside, meaty, best sliced and sauteed with butter, roasted, or cooked as chips.

Name: Roots: Rutabaga
Body: Rutabaga by the lb - a hearty winter vegetable, roast or mash these bad boys for a nice (and lower carb) alternative to potatoes!

Name: Roots: Carrots - per lb.
Body: Sweet, orange carrots by the lb.

Name: Salad Radish
Body: Fresh-harvested salad radishes, a bunch containing 8-10 pieces.

Name: Hakurei Turnips
Body: Sweet hakurei turnips, or salad turnips, in a fresh-picked bunch.  Great when sliced raw on a salad, or can be stir-fried for a sweet addition to any dish.

Name: Purple Daikon Radishes - per lb.
Body: Purple Daikon radishes have a mild, sweet, and peppery flavor well suited for raw, cooked, and pickled preparations. The radishes can be eaten with or without the skin, and when raw, the flesh can be thinly sliced and incorporated into salads, used as a raw vessel for dips, or chopped and mixed into slaws. The brilliant, bi-colored flesh adds visual appeal to sandwiches, appetizer plates, sashimi, and pickled preparations, or it can be coarsely grated using a special Japanese grater as a condiment.

Name: Roots: Pink Daikon Radish
Body: Beautiful red/pink Daikon radish - Mild, crisp, and juicy.   Great for fresh eating, pickling, kimchi, and roasting.  Price is per pound

Name: Microgreens: Sunflower Shoots
Body: Fresh sunflower shoots, cur straight from the greenhouse. Nutty, crisp, and sweet. In 3.5 ounce clamshell.

Name: Microgreens: Spicy Microgreens
Body: A medley of three types of spicy radish microgreens. Add a zing to your salad or meal! In a 2 ounce clamshell

Name: Microgreens: Sweet Pea Shoots
Body: Perfect addition to salads, sandwiches, soups, and more. Tasty as a just-off-the-vine snap pea. In a 3 ounce clamshell
